Supernested is a test of nested KVM.  It is able to run KVM, nested to
any depth, limited only by available memory, bugs in KVM, and your
patience.


Author
----------------------------------------------------------------------

By Richard W.M. Jones <rjones@redhat.com>

Bugs, feedback etc: http://www.redhat.com/mailman/listinfo/virt-tools-list

(Note: Bugs in KVM or the kernel should be reported to the qemu-devel
or Linux kernel mailing lists respectively)


